0Boeing's%20home%20turf.%20Eastern%20then%20ordered%2023%20A300s%20for%20%24778%20million%2C%20pleased%20with%20its%20lower%20fuel%20consumption%2C%20per%20The%20Washington%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20The%20fly-by-wire%20A320%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222997%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Prince%20Charles%20and%20Princess%20Diana%20of%20Wales%20pour%20champagne%20on%20the%20nose%20of%20the%20Airbus%EF%BF%BD%20latest%20model%2C%20the%20A-320%20during%20the%20christening%20ceremony%20at%20Toulouse-Blagnac%20airport%2C%20southern%20France%2C%20Feb.%2015%2C%201987.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ba2b4c780eb35532d8b5343%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222016%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrince%20Charles%20and%20Princess%20Diana%20launch%20the%20first%20A320.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FLionel%20Cironneau%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAirbus%20didn't%20find%20real%20success%20until%20the%20advent%20of%20the%20single-aisle%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbus-a320-history-boeing-737-rival-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA320%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201987.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20first%20jet%20rolled%20out%20of%20the%20factory%20in%20Toulouse%2C%20France%2C%20it%20was%20christened%20by%20Prince%20Charles%20and%20Princess%20Diana%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20sign%20that%20Airbus%20wasn't%20messing%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20A320's%20real%20genius%20was%20using%20fly-by-wire%20technology%20only%20found%20in%20fighter%20jets%20and%20Concorde%20until%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20replaces%20mechanical%20flight%20controls%20with%20computer-controlled%20systems%20to%20process%20the%20pilots'%20input%20and%20is%20considered%20safer%20because%20there%20are%20fewer%20points%20of%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%20it's%20cheaper%20for%20operators%20because%20computers%20are%20easier%20to%20fix%2C%20and%20fewer%20parts%20and%20lighter%20wires%20meant%20better%20fuel%20efficiency%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20A320%20went%20on%20to%20become%20the%20world's%20second-best-selling%20airliner%2C%20behind%20the%20Boeing%20737.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Government%20subsidies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22U.S.%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%20addresses%20Boeing%20employees%2022%20February%201993%20in%20Washington.%20The%20nose%20of%20the%20latest%20Boeing%20747-400%20cargo%20plane%20is%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65aa71636979d7371824976e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22639%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBill%20Clinton%20addresses%20Boeing%20employees%20in%201993.%3Cp%3EPAUL%20RICHARDS%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Airbus%20started%20to%20become%20a%20threat%20to%20Boeing%2C%20it%20began%20to%20face%20more%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201993%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fbusiness%2F1993%2F02%2F25%2Fclinton-stirs-new-furor-over-airbus-subsidy%2Ffc7cd294-1779-4d39-8032-44e976ce2880%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBill%20Clinton%20provoked%20tensions%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20he%20visited%20Boeing's%20factory%20after%20it%20announced%20layoffs%2C%20the%20Post%20reported%20at%20the%20time.%20The%20president%20blamed%20Airbus%20for%20the%20American%20company's%20troubles%20and%20he%20criticized%20the%20billions%20in%20subsidies%20that%20Airbus%20received%20from%20European%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbus%20and%20the%20governments%20denied%20those%20claims%2C%20before%20a%20trade%20war%20ensued%20as%20both%20sides%20imposed%20tariffs%20on%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20US%20held%20talks%20with%20the%20UK%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20and%20Spain%20in%202004%2C%20it%20filed%20a%20complaint%20with%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organization.%20The%20European%20Union%20also%20filed%20a%20tit-for-tat%20lawsuit%20accusing%20the%20US%20of%20giving%20unfair%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fhighlights-17-year-airbus-boeing-trade-war-2021-06-15%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubsidies%20to%20Boeing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20per%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dispute%20took%20no%20less%20than%2017%20years%20to%20be%20resolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20WTO%20found%20that%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fustr.gov%2Fabout-us%2Fpolicy-offices%2Fpress-office%2Fpress-releases%2F2019%2Foctober%2Fus-wins-75-billion-award-airbus%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirbus%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Fcommission%2Fpresscorner%2Fdetail%2Fen%2Fip_20_1895%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoeing%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20illegally%20received%20billions%20in%20government%20subsidies%2C%20and%20permitted%20tariffs%20to%20be%20imposed%20as%20a%20consequence.%20A%20truce%20was%20struck%20in%202021%20to%20end%20the%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20The%20A320neo%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224102%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Airbus%20A320neo%20takes%20off%20for%20its%20first%20test%20flight%2C%20on%20September%2025%2C%202014%20in%20Blagnac%20near%20Toulouse.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65aa6cdedcdb354a9858da46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222676%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Airbus%20A320neo's%20first%20test%20flight%20in%202014.%3Cp%3EERIC%20CABANIS%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAirbus%20introduced%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20its%20popular%20short-haul%20A320%20jet%2C%20and%20it%20was%20quick%20to%20make%20a%20mark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20neo%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bnew%20engine%20option%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20was%20so%20popular%20because%20it%20was%20quieter%2C%20more%20fuel%20efficient%2C%20and%20therefore%20cheaper%20for%20airlines%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20large%20winglets%2C%20more%20than%207%20feet%20high%2C%20also%20helped%20