rget%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eharder%20to%20find%20a%20job%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%20than%20last%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20Zhao%2C%20lead%20economist%20for%20jobs%20search%20platform%20Glassdoor%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20hasn't%20released%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-rate-job-growth-labor-market-wages-december-economic-outlook-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eemployment%20or%20hiring%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20statistics%20just%20yet%20for%202024.%20However%2C%20data%20for%202023%20shows%20job%20openings%20cooled%20down%20and%20average%20monthly%20job%20growth%20was%20smaller%20than%20it%20was%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPayroll%20employment%20rose%20by%202.7%20million%20last%20year%2C%20for%20an%20average%20monthly%20gain%20of%20225%2C000%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fempsit.nr0.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enews%20release%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20BLS%20stated.%20However%2C%20that%20lags%20behind%202022's%20increase%20of%204.8%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20job%20numbers%20don't%20tell%20the%20whole%20story.%20Zhao%20said%20there%20are%20other%20factors%20that%20could%20%26quot%3Bbuoy%20sentiment%20about%20the%20job%20market%20in%20the%20new%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-up-how-consumer-price-index-looked-december-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einflation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20comes%20down%20and%20people%20start%20to%20look%20past%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-prediction-goldman-sachs-economic-growth-gdp-wall-street-economy-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erecession%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20that%20should%20help%20improve%20overall%20sentiment%20among%20workers%20and%20employers%20alike%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20may%20give%20job%20seekers%20the%20confidence%20that%20they%20can%20land%20better%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Croucher%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%2C%20head%20of%20North%20America%20marketing%20and%20sales%20enablement%20at%20ManpowerGroup%2C%20said%20finding%20work%20%26quot%3Bis%20going%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20hard%20unless%20you%20have%20the%20right%20skills.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20people%20invest%20their%20time%20and%20really%20understand%20what%20are%20some%20shortage%20areas%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20hiring%20and%20people%20with%20skills%2C%20I%20think%20it'll%20be%20easier%20to%20get%20a%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Croucher%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhao%2C%20Croucher%2C%20and%20career%20coach%20Stacey%20Perkins%20outlined%20four%20tips%20for%20job%20seekers%20in%20today's%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20a%20job%20plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPerkins%2C%20a%20career%20coach%20at%20organizational%20consulting%20firm%20Korn%20Ferry%2C%20suggested%20job%20seekers%20figure%20out%20a%20robust%20strategy%20for%20job%20searching%2C%20which%20doesn't%20mean%20simply%20submitting%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20to%20many%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20involve%20making%20a%20list%20of%20employers%20you%20actually%20want%20to%20work%20for.%20Perkins%20suggested%20looking%20at%20who%20you%20have%20a%20mutual%20connection%20with%20or%20identifying%20who%20you%20already%20know%20at%20the%20places%20noted%20on%20the%20list.%20That%20way%2C%20even%20if%20there%20isn't%20an%20opening%20just%20yet%2C%20you%20have%20already%20taken%20a%20step%20in%20making%20yourself%20known%20to%20the%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20be%20the%20one%20that%20they're%20thinking%20about%20because%20you've%20started%20building%20some%20of%20those%20relationships%2C%26quot%3B%20Perkins%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20people%20who%20may%20have%20a%20career%20gap%2C%20Perkins%20said%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20do%20want%20to%20see%20that%20you've%20done%20something.%26quot%3B%20Because%20of%20this%2C%20Perkins%20suggested%20volunteering%20or%20doing%20a%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerkins%20added%20that%20applicants%20should%20follow%20up%20with%20a%20note%20after%20submitting%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20but%20avoid%20writing%20a%20repeat%20cover%20letter.%20Instead%2C%20focus%20on%20a%20few%20highlights%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20just%20put%20your%20application%20in%20and%20just%20sit%20and%20wait%2C%26quot%3B%20Perkins%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20find%20a%20recruiter%2C%20the%20potential%20hiring%20manager%2C%20or%20somebody%20who%20might%20be%20a%20decision-maker%20and%20just%20send%20them%20a%20quick%20note.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20people%20just%20graduating%20and%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20Croucher%20suggested%20looking%20for%20an%20internship%20first%20because%20it%20could%20be%20easier%20to%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20always%20possible%20to%20predict%20which%20industry%20will%20do%20well%20or%20do%20poorly%20in%20a%20given%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20to%20do%20your%20research%26quot%3B%20of%20industries%20and%20companies%20that%20are%20doing%20well%20before%20job%20searching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETry%20networking%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZhao%20said%20online%20resources%20where%20people%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glassdoor.com%2FCompare%2Findex.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompare%20employers%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20one%20way%20to%20determine%20if%20a%20company%20would%20be%20a%20good%20fit%2C%20but%20another%20way%20is%20through%20networking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENetworking%20can%20include%20talking%20to%20different%20people%20who%20may%20work%20where%20you're%20hoping%20to%20get%20a%20job%20%E2%80%94%20from%20alumni%20to%20friends%20and%20family%2C%20Perkins%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20when%20you%20find%20somebody%20where%20you%20already%20have%20something%20in%20common%2C%20again%20like%20alumni%2C%20or%20you're%20part%20of%20a%20book%20club%20or%20a%20running%20club%20or%20something%20like%20that%2C%20then%20it's%20easier%20just%20to%20strike%20up%20the%20conversation%2C%26quot%3B%20Perkins%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20job%20seekers%20sending%20cold%20messages%2C%20Perkins%20advises%20against%20just%20writing%20that%20you're%20interested%20in%20a%20job%20at%20the%20company%20and%20asking%20if%20they%20can%20help.%20Instead%2C%20highlight%20something%20from%20their%20profile%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20reached%20out%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETry%20sending%20a%20video%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20can%20try%20creating%20a%20video%20about%20themselves%20as%20one%20way%20to%20potentially%20be%20distinct%20from%20others%20applying%20for%20the%20same%20role.%20Croucher%20said%20it's%20similar%20to%20a%20cover%20letter%20%E2%80%94%20just%20in%20a%20different%20format.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20it's%20somebody%20willing%20to%20take%20a%20risk%20and%20do%20something%20different%20to%20stand%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Croucher%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20a%20skill%20in%20and%20of%20itself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECroucher%20said%20the%20video%20is%20really%20about%20a%20job%20candidate%20showcasing%20being%20comfortable%20talking%20about%20themselves%20and%20also%20can%20be%20a%20first%20impression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20really%20what%20would%20make%20you%20stand%20out%20and%20really%20talking%20about%20why%20you're%20interested%20in%20the%20job%20and%20showing%20some%20passion%20for%20that%20specific%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Croucher%20said.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20when%20I%20hire%20people%2C%20I%20want%20to%20hire%20people%20that%20are%20passionate%20about%20what%20they%20do%20because%20then%20they%20take%20more%20pride%20and%20work%20ethic%20is%20usually%20higher.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETry%20adding%20information%20to%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnother%20big%20thing%20in%20this%20market%20is%20to%20keep%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%20updated%2C%26quot%3B%20Perkins%20said%2C%20noting%20things%20like%20certifications%20are%20good%20to%20add.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20new%20to%20working%20right%20out%20of%20college%20or%20you're%20trying%20to%20change%20careers%2C%20I%20do%20think%20it's%20important%20to%20have%20the%20certifications%20and%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20Croucher%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20job%20seekers%20should%20be%20picky%20about%20what%20they%20want%20to%20include.%20Croucher%20said%20that%20putting%20too%20much%20detail%20could%20%26quot%3Bcut%20themselves%20out%20of%20the%20running%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-get-job-this-year-network-resume-skills-certificates-unemployment-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705748881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a827fedcdb354a985852e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-get-job-this-year-network-resume-skills-certificates-unemployment-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Three%20career%20experts%20share%20what%20job%20seekers%20should%20do%20if%20they%20want%20to%20get%20a%20new%20job%20this%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-get-job-this-year-network-resume-skills-certificates-unemployment-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amid%20troop%20influx%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20says%20India%20to%20put%20up%20fence%20along%20Myanmar%20border%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%