go%20city%20limits%20in%20Orange%20County.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%202022%2C%20they%20got%20the%20news%20that%20would%20make%20renters%20everywhere%20shiver%3A%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20rent%20on%20their%202%2C300-square-foot%20house%20was%20going%20up%20from%20a%20little%20under%20%243%2C500%20a%20month%20to%20just%20over%20%245%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20just%20like%2C%20we%20just%20can't%20do%20it%20anymore.%20Literally%2C%20we%20can't%20afford%20a%20%241%2C500%20a%20month%20increase%20in%20rent%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicole%2C%20who%20works%20in%20advocacy%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20rent%20hike%20that%20broke%20the%20dam%20for%20them%20and%20some%20of%20their%20peers.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCUUR0000SEHA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esummer%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rent%20inflation%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewas%20almost%207%25%20higher%20than%20the%20year%20prior.%20Once%20they%20began%20talking%20to%20their%20friends%20about%20just%20how%20costly%20it%20was%2C%20friends%20began%20to%20reveal%20they%20were%20in%20a%20similar%20position%20%E2%80%94%20and%20started%20to%20scatter%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20and%20her%20family%20decided%20to%20leave.%20It%20just%20wasn't%20feasible%20for%20them%20anymore%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20was%20really%20heartbreaking%20because%20we%20were%20in%20walking%20distance%20of%20the%20elementary%20school%20that%20my%20son%20was%20supposed%20to%20go%20to.%26quot%3B%20They%20moved%20the%20summer%20before%20he%20started%20kindergarten.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20done%20orientation%20there.%20We%20had%20been%20taking%20him%20to%20play%20on%20the%20playground%20there%20so%20he%20could%20get%20acclimated%20to%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20like%2C%20'Just%20kidding.%20We%20have%20to%20move%20across%20the%20country%20now.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20story%20that's%20playing%20out%20for%20renters%20nationwide%2C%20especially%20those%20in%20California.%20The%20Golden%20State%20is%20becoming%20particularly%20inaccessible%20for%20younger%20homebuyers%2C%20who%20have%20seen%20their%20homeownership%20rates%20tumble%20over%20the%20last%20few%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fternercenter.berkeley.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2FHomeownership-Ladder-May-2023-Final.pdf%3Futm_source%3Dnewsletter%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3Dnewsletter_axiosam%26stream%3Dtop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epaper%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Terner%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Innovation%20at%20UC%20Berkeley%20found%2C%20looking%20at%202020%20data%2C%20that%20homeownership%20rates%20among%2025-%20to%2045-year-olds%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-real-estate-housing-millennial-homeownership-population-shrinking-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eplummeted%20the%20most%20out%20of%20all%20age%20groups%20since%201980%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20housing%20prices%20in%20the%20state%20had%20remained%20commensurate%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20over%20the%20last%2020%20or%20so%20years%2C%20it%20could%20have%20averted%20half%20the%20decline%20in%20California's%20homeownership%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20as%20BI's%20Noah%20Sheidlower%20reported%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-from-california-pros-cons-texas-millennials-gen-z-single-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20typical%20mover%20out%20of%20California%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20likely%20a%20Gen%20Zer%20or%20a%20millennial.%20Those%20former%20residents%20are%20setting%20out%20for%20places%20like%20Florida%2C%20Arizona%2C%20and%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20staying%20with%20family%20for%20a%20few%20months%20in%20Florida%20to%20get%20their%20feet%20under%20them%20and%20build%20up%20some%20savings%2C%20Nicole%20and%20her%20family%20decided%20to%20move%20somewhere%20that%20better%20suited%20their%20needs.%20In%20the%20summer%20of%202023%2C%20they%20landed%20in%20Richmond%2C%20Virginia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20California%2C%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Blovely%20move%20in%20the%20right%20direction%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20remember%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20gas%20prices%20got%20up%20to%20%247%20a%20gallon%20where%20we%20were%20living%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Food%20costs%20were%20hefty%20in%20California%2C%20too%3A%20She%20joked%20that%20just%20crossing%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20threshold%20of%20a%20grocery%20store%20cost%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%24185.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20Richmond%20is%20much%20more%20reasonable%20in%20terms%20of%20cost%20of%20living.%20Rent%20is%20what%20I%20would%20consider%20within%20normal%20limits%20%E2%80%94%20groceries%2C%20gas%2C%20utilities%2C%20all%20that%20stuff.%20It's%20much%20more%20affordable%20for%20us%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicole%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedian%20gross%20rent%20in%20Richmond%20was%20%241%2C192%20in%202022%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.census.gov%2Ftable%2FACSDP1Y2022.DP04%3Fq%3Ddp04%26g%3D050XX00US06059_160XX00US5167000%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECensus%20Bureau's%20American%20Community%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20compared%20to%20%242%2C251%20in%20Orange%20County%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20said%20she'd%20love%20to%20stay%20in%20Richmond%2C%20although%20she's%20not%20sure%20if%20homeownership%20will%20be%20in%20the%20cards%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20fellow%20millennials%20who%20are%20stuck%20in%20a%20similar%20position%2C%20Nicole%20takes%20some%20comfort%20in%20knowing%20that%20this%20situation%20isn't%20unique.%20She%20and%20her%20husband%20did%20things%20they%20were%20supposed%20to%20do%20%E2%80%94%20got%20their%20degrees%2C%20went%20to%20law%20school%20%E2%80%94%20and%20yet%2C%20here%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20go%20to%20school%2C%20you%20graduate%2C%20you%20get%20a%20good%20job%2C%20you%20get%20a%20house.%20That's%20the%20path%20we%20thought%20we%20were%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20between%20our%20combined%20student%20loans%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20buying%20these%20days%2C%20it's%20just%20not%20happened%20for%20us%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20wishes%20older%20generations%20understood%20that%20millennials%20are%20dealing%20with%20compounding%20economic%20issues.%20After%20all%2C%20many%20millennials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-say-they-cant-afford-dream-life-survey-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeel%20like%3C%2Fa%3E%20they'll%20never%20make%20enough%20money%20to%20get%20what%20they%20want%20in%20life%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-millennials-debt-financial-security-interest-rates-recession-savings-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etheir%20sense%20of%20financial%20well-being%20is%20tanking%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20that%20almost%20every%20millennial%20I%20know%2C%20myself%20included%2C%20is%20remarkably%20hardworking%20and%20conscientious%20and%20responsible%20and%20that%20it's%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20not%20saving%20enough%20or%20not%20being%20smart%20with%20our%20money%20or%20not%20finding%20our%20bootstraps.%20It's%20that%20life%20has%20gotten%20so%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BGroceries%20are%20more%20expensive%2C%20gas%20is%20more%20expensive%2C%20rent%20is%20more%20expensive.%20Interest%20for%20a%20mortgage%20is%20not%20going%20to%20probably%20be%20below%207%25%20anytime%20soon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20millennial%20or%20Californian%20(or%20both)%20struggling%20to%20find%20or%20afford%20housing%3F%20Did%20you%20move%20in%20