F2024%2Fshopping%2Fnews%2Fwatch-nhl-pro-hockey-games-streaming-online-1235833129%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22PBS%20SoCal%20Rebrands%20Sister%20Public%20Broadcaster%20KCET%20As%20%E2%80%98PBS%20SoCal%20Plus%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705715862000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FPBS-SoCAL-logo.jpeg%3Fw%3D993%26h%3D554%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235879870%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CKCET%E2%80%9D%20is%20infinitely%20no%20more.%20Well%2C%20sort%20of.%20The%20Los%20Angeles-based%20public%20broadcaster%20still%20exists%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9CKCET%E2%80%9D%20remains%20its%20legal%20call%20letters.%20But%20effective%20Tuesday%2C%20Feb.%206%2C%20the%20station%20will%20start%20branding%20itself%20as%20%E2%80%9CPBS%20SoCal%20Plus.%E2%80%9D%20That%20brings%20it%20further%20in%20line%20with%20its%20sister%20station%20PBS%20SoCal%20(KOCE-TV)%2C%20with%20which%20it%20merged%20in%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Varietyschneider%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fpbs-socal-kcet-rebrand-pbs-socal-plus-1235879870%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fpbs-socal-kcet-rebrand-pbs-socal-plus-1235879870%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fpbs-socal-kcet-rebrand-pbs-socal-plus-1235879870%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rohingya%20Refugees%20File%20PIL%20Against%20Facebook%20in%20Delhi%20High%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F07151938%2FWhatsApp-Image-2022-08-07-at-1.35.28-PM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%202019%2C%20Equality%20Labs%2C%20an%20advocacy%20group%20that%20focuses%20on%20technology%20and%20human%20rights%2C%20with%20a%20team%20of%C2%A020%20international%20researchers%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0that%20included%20Dalits%2C%20Muslims%2C%20Christians%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20and%20others%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fequalitylabs.wpengine.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FFacebook_India_Report_Equality_Labs.pdf%5C%22%3Esystematically%20recorded%3C%2Fa%3E%201%2C000%20Facebook%20posts%20that%20they%20found%20to%20be%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20platform%E2%80%99s%20community%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20findings%20displayed%20that%20over%2040%25%20of%20all%20the%20posts%20that%20were%20removed%20after%20the%20group%20reported%20them%20were%20restored%20after%20a%20period%20of%2090%20days%20on%20average.%C2%A0An%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20the%20posts%20that%20were%20restored%20were%20Islamophobic%20in%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20summarises%20Equality%20Labs%E2%80%99%20advocacy%20concerning%20hate%20speech%20on%20Facebook%20during%202018%20and%20reveals%20disturbingly%20real%20threats%20that%20Facebook%20content%20presents%20to%20an%20estimated%20300%20million%20Indian%20caste%2C%20religious%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20queer%20minorities%20both%20in%20India%20and%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeeping%20their%20own%20experiences%20battling%20hate%20and%20the%20Equality%20Labs%20report%20in%20mind%2C%20Rohingya%20refugees%20have%20filed%20a%20Public%20Interest%20Petition%20(PIL)%20under%20Article%20226%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20invoking%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Rohingya%20community%20in%20India%20seeking%20protection%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20as%20members%20of%20their%20community%20in%20Delhi%20and%20throughout%20the%20country%20face%20violence%2C%20sometimes%20escalating%20to%20physical%20threats%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20dissemination%20of%20violent%20hate%20remarks%20targeting%20them%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20their%20ethnicity%20and%20religion%20on%20Facebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%20of%20the%20PIL%20are%20Rohingya%20refugees%20who%20fled%20Myanmar%20due%20to%20ethnic%20violence%20and%20have%20been%20residing%20in%20New%20Delhi%20for%20the%20past%202%20to%205%20years%20and%20have%20been%20issued%20valid%20identity%20cards%20by%20the%20UNHCR%2C%20The%20UN%20Refugee%20Agency%2C%20which%20recognises%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20community%20as%20a%20persecuted%20community.%20The%20Rohingya%20people%20are%20a%20Muslim%20minority%20from%20the%20Rakhine%20state%20of%20Myanmar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20argues%20that%20the%20origins%20of%20these%20posts%20targeting%20them%20are%20in%20India%2C%20and%20the%20petitioners%20are%20affected%20by%20%E2%80%98Facebook%E2%80%99s%E2%80%99%20failure%20to%20take%20an%20action%20against%20hate%20speech%20on%20its%20platform.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20note%20that%2C%20as%20of%202023%2C%20the%20UNHCR%20reported%20that%20India%20was%20sheltering%20approximately%2074%2C600%20Rohingya%20refugees%20from%20Myanmar%2C%20more%20than%20an%20estimated%2054%2C100%20of%20whom%20entered%20since%20the%20coup%20in%20February%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20presence%20of%20Rohingya%20refugees%20in%20India%20is%20a%20highly%20politicised%20matter%2C%20and%20as%20such%20they%20are%20disproportionately%20targeted%20with%20harmful%20content%20on%20Facebook%20painting%20the%20group%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20India%2C%20often%20referring%20to%20the%20group%20as%20%E2%80%9Cterrorists%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cinfiltrators%E2%80%9D%20and%20exaggerating%20the%20numbers%20of%20Rohingya%20that%20have%20fled%20to%20India.%20A%202019%20study%20into%20hate%20speech%20on%20Facebook%20in%20India%2C%20found%20that%206%25%20of%20Islamophobic%20posts%20were%20specifically%20anti-Rohingya%20%E2%80%93%20when%20the%20Rohingya%20comprised%20only%200.02%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Muslim%20population%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20records%20how%20several%20Facebook%20users%20in%20India%20often%20used%20the%20terms%20such%20as%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98illegal%20migrants%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98enemies%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Bangladeshis%E2%80%99%20to%20target%20the%20Rohingya%20who%20are%20predominantly%20Muslim.%20Certain%20users%20also%20advocated%20for%20the%20use%20of%20%E2%80%98bulldozers%E2%80%99%20to%20wreck%20homes%20of%20these%20%E2%80%98enemies%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99.%20Some%20Indian%20users%20on%20Facebook%20would%20also%20spread%20misinformation%20about%20Rohingyas%20running%20abduction%20and%20organ%20sale%20rackets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEva%20Buzo%2C%20a%20barrister%20providing%20support%20for%20the%20petitioning%20counsel%2C%20feels%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20file%20this%20petition%20because%20a%20repetition%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20type%20of%20harmful%20content%20that%20was%20proliferating%20on%20Facebook%20against%20the%20Rohingya%20in%20Myanmar%20in%20the%20lead%20up%20to%20the%20incidents%20in%202017.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20being%20an%20election%20ear%20and%20considering%20that%20Facebook%20operates%20in%20a%20way%20that%20really%20highlights%20political%20divisiveness%2C%20so%20filing%20the%20petition%20now%20is%20a%20form%20of%20preventative%20action%20to%20prevent%20the%20situation%20of%20harmful%20content%20being%20spread%20about%20the%20Rohingyas%20in%20India%2C%20so%20that%20it%20does%20not%20reach%20a%20point%20of%20actual%20violence%20against%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20Buzo%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Buzo%20was%20also%20a%20part%20of%20running%20a%20case%20in%20Ireland%20against%20Facebook%20for%20its%20role%20in%20the%202017%20violence%20against%20the%20Rohingya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBuzo%20also%20said%20that%20in%20countries%20like%20India%2C%20which%20haven%E2%80%99t%20signed%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unhcr.org%2Fin%2Fabout-unhcr%2Fwho-we-are%2F1951-refugee-convention%5C%22%3ERefugee%20Convention%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Rohingya%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20same%20rights%20as%20refugees%20in%20the%20countries%20where%20the%20convention%20is%20applicable%2C%20that%20leaves%20them%20extremely%20vulnerable.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20can%20be%20removed%20any%20minute%2C%20they%20can%20be%20targeted%2C%20this%20increases%20their%20vulnerability%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%202023%2C%20when%20the%20Nuh%20communal%20violence%20on%20July%2031%20shook%20the%20region%20with%20events%20of%20shops%2C%20homes%20and%20places%20of%20worship%20belonging%20to%20Muslims%20being%20vandalised%2C%20set%20ablaze%20and%20looted%3B%20the%20Rohingya%20as%20a%20community%20felt%20deeply%20vulnerable%20and%20easy%20targets%20of%20local%20ire%20and%20state%20law.%20They%20had%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Frohingya-refugees-detained-after-nuh-violence-others-living-in-fear%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20Foreigners%20Regional%20Registration%20Office%20(FRRO)%20officers%20came%20to%20their%20shanties%20and%20took%20many%20of%20them%20to%20Delhi%20for%20questioning%20in%20relation%20with%20the%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDrawing%20on%20reports%20from%20Amnesty%20International%20also%20established%20that%20history%20shows%20Facebook%20is%20not%20willing%20to%20act%20on%20warnings%20so%20Buzo%20and%20the%20petitioning%20council%20felt%20need%20to%20seek%20an%20injunction%20from%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvocate%20Kawalpreet%20Kaur%2C%20who%20is%20representing%20the%20Rohingya%20petitioners%20in%20court%2C%20said%20that%20the%20petition%20had%20been%20filed%20keeping%20in%20view%20the%20role%20Facebook%20has%20been%20playing%20in%20India%20promoting%20divisive%20content%20against%20minorities%20especially%20the%20Rohingya%20community.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20posts%20are%20originating%20in%20India%20and%20have%20tremendous%20potential%20for%20causing%20real%20time%20violence.%20The%20examples%20are%20quite%20apparent%20in%20the%20context%20of%20frequent%20statements%20made%20against%20the%20Rohingya%20community%20residing%20in%20India%2C%20targeting%20of%20their%20slum%20settlements%20and%20the%20violence%20which%20these%20posts%20on%20Facebook%20can%20lead%20to%20as%20we%20saw%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kaur%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20important%20reason%20that%20Kaur%20flags%20behind%20filing%20this%20petition%20is%20in%20context%20of%20the%20impending%20elections.%20Kaur%20shared%20that%20there%20is%20extreme%20alarm%20among%20the%20Rohingya%20community%20residing%20here%20as%20they%20are%20afraid%20of%20the%20immense%20number%20of%20vitriolic%20posts%20that%20would%20be%20posted%20and%20circulated%20on%20Facebook%20targeting%20them.%20%E2%80%9COur%20aim%20is%20to%20hold%20entities%20like%20Facebook%20responsible%20so%20that%20they%20do%20not%20selectively%20apply%20their%20community%20standards%20and%20not%20omit%20their%20responsibility%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20protection%20of%20minorities%20community.%20Facebook%20is%20actually%20playing%20a%20public%20role%20here%20and%20thus%2C%20we%20have%20decided%20to%20take%20it%20to%20court%20directly%20in%20Delhi%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kaur%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20is%20listed%20for%20January%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705714245000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F07151938%2FWhatsApp-Image-2022-08-07-at-1.35.28-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Frohingya-refugees-file-pil-against-facebook-in-delhi-high-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20petition%20records%20how%20several%20Facebook%20users%20in%20India%20often%20used%20the%20terms%20such%20as%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%98illegal%20migrants%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98enemies%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Bangladeshis%E2%80%99%20to%20target%20the%20Rohingya%20who%20are%20predominantly%20Muslim.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2